tip.text: A dozen of standard oysters and a cup of world famous mussel chowder overseeing the coromandel bay. THE BEST!
Large mixed meat kebab with garlic yogurt & mild chili sauces is da bomb!
Ambience, service and food were excellent. Don't forget to tip the servers.
The kimchi stew with pork belly or tuna is a absolute must try.
Definitely the ribs & chips for lunch.
Quiet place to spend the night. There's camper van parking.
Deep fried Mince chicken on bread and tom yum soup is a must!
Best Taiwanese desert and milk tea!
Hokkien char is good. Love the pork lard! Banana fritters was alright. Similar to a donut.
Donuts is an absolutely must try!
Lunch deal ramen is a must try!
Try the claypot pig stomach. Not for the faint hearted though.
Assam laksa is delicious, pretty close to the authentic dish.
Noodle soup is a MUST try! Very thick soup base. Go for the large bowl.
